CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1945, pg. 24 reads: "Kiddie Party - A birthday party was given recently for Dian Ilona Walker, three-year-old daughter of Pfc. and Mrs. James C. Walker, at 268 Paulson Avenue. Guests were Marian Baker, John Baker, Arbutus, Patricia and Quintella Cathie; Barbara and Audrey Ficklin, Helene Fisher, Diana Blackwell, Henry Walker Jr., Patricia Anderson, Lloyd Thornton, William Page Jr., Donna Strayhorn, Barbara Jean Saunders, Madeline Formley, Joyce Walker, Bobby and Billy Cogdall, and Sonny and Jean Weatherly. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dian Ilona Walker blowing out candles on birthday cake, in home of Pfc. and Mrs. James C. Walker, 268 Paulson Avenue
